                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre; irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Śǝllāse. Walda
                        Śǝ[llase] is the name of the scribe mentioned in the supplication formula on
                           <locus target="#2ra">2ra</locus> (partly erased).<date>19th century
                           (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>፪ሆሙ is used on <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus> l.1.</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Two lines on the incipit of the text, alternating
                           with a black line; the name of Māryām and of Yoḥannǝs; the name of the
                           donor and of the scribe; elements of Ethiopic numerals and of punctuation
                           signs.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 8rb, 8va, 16va. - Immediate corrections indicated by dots around the word: e.g., fols. 8rb, 10vb, 11ra, 16vb. - Immediate correction indicated by thin lines above and below the word: <locus target="#9vb">fol.  9vb</locus>. - Crude drawing of a cross in blue pen on <locus target="#18v">fol.  18v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Both boards are missing (possibly the bookblock never
                           had any).
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
